# CONSTRAINTS_INDEX.md

**Version:** 1.0 | **Last Updated:** March 2026 | **Owner:** CEO + CTO
**Load this file first** in any session that requires constraint awareness. Use it to determine which specific constraint files to load for the task at hand. Do not load all constraint files simultaneously — load only what the task requires.

---

## Constraint Files & When to Load Them

| File | Load When |
|---|---|
| `CONSTRAINTS_ARCHITECTURE.md` | Any task touching infrastructure, deployment, framework, stack, or database decisions |
| `CONSTRAINTS_DATA_SECURITY.md` | Any task touching auth, logging, secrets, API keys, warfighter data, or PII |
| `CONSTRAINTS_DATA_ACCESS.md` | Any task involving multi-tenancy, RLS policies, OEM data feeds, telemetry ingestion, or the feedback loop |
| `CONSTRAINTS_API_INTEGRATIONS.md` | Any task involving API design, external integrations, OEM data ingestion, or webhooks |
| `CONSTRAINTS_PRODUCT_SCOPE.md` | Any feature scoping, PRD writing, issue creation, or product decision |
| `CONSTRAINTS_UX.md` | Any task involving UI design, frontend components, warfighter features, or mobile experience |

---

## Slash Command Load Map

Use this table to determine which constraint files to load per Cursor slash command:

| Command | Load These Files |
|---|---|
| `/create-issue` | `CONSTRAINTS_PRODUCT_SCOPE.md` |
| `/explore` | `CONSTRAINTS_ARCHITECTURE.md` |
| `/plan` | `CONSTRAINTS_ARCHITECTURE.md` + `CONSTRAINTS_PRODUCT_SCOPE.md` |
| `/execute` | `CONSTRAINTS_ARCHITECTURE.md` + `CONSTRAINTS_DATA_SECURITY.md` + `CONSTRAINTS_DATA_ACCESS.md` + `CONSTRAINTS_API_INTEGRATIONS.md` (load UX and others if feature touches those domains) |
| `/review` | All constraint files |
| `/doc-update` | `CONSTRAINTS_PRODUCT_SCOPE.md` |

